<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-766-188  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 766 188.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  August 6 1990 n602 p4(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fujitsu acquires ICL: pays $1.37B for 80% stake. (InternationalComputers Ltd)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woolnough, Roger.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fujitsu Ltd acquired 80 percent of International Computers Ltd(ICL) in mid-1990, which it says it will continue to run with theexisting management.andP;  ICL is a subsidiary of Britain's STC plc,which collected $1.37 billion in the deal.andP;  Fujitsu wants toattract other European investors to the company and plans to floatsome of its shares on the London Stock Exchange within the nextfew years.andP;  STC will use the cash from the transaction toestablish itself as a world player in the transmission systemsmarket.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Fujitsu Ltd. (acquisitions and mergers)STC PLC (acquisitions and mergers)International Computers Ltd. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Topic:     AcquisitionMarketing StrategyInternational TradeHardware Vendors.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   How Europe's computer makers stack up. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>